title: For Sale/Trade:  Price Reduced! Gibbs Springfield 1903A4 Sniper rifle and 100 30.06 rounds
postcontent:
Gibbs Springfield 1903A4 Sniper Rifle. This rifle is SUPER clean with only 15-20 rounds through it. Shoots strait and kicks hard. I also have 100 rounds of 30.06 specifically made for this rifle and or a M-1 Garand. This rifle has zero blemishes and is in prestine condition. 
The Gibbs M1903A4 is built using original Remington-made World War II M1903A3 actions and turned-down bolts, which Gibbs obtained large quantities of when it purchase the rifle division of Parker-Hale in the 1990's. Gibbs then utilizes new-made 4-groove barrels made identical to the originals. Each receiver is carefully drilled and tapped using replicas of the original "Redfield" rings and mounts and an exact copy of the M73B1 scope, used on the 1st model M1903A4's. Each barreled action has the original military parkerized finish with polished blue stock furniture, again, identical to the originals.

The stocks are new-made "C" configuration with a linseed oil finish and have replica cartouches similar to the originals.

Each gun comes with a replica of the M1907 U.S. issued leather sling and OD Green canvas carrying case. The result is a firearm that comes out of the box in brand-new condition, ready for shooting, display, reenacting and field use. Not just exceptional in looks and finish, each gun is made to hold to the accuracy standards of the U.S. Government during World War II. "We want our customers to know that they can achieve the same accuracy as World War II snipers with these guns" stated Val Forgett, President of Forgett Militaria, LLC.

Like all replicas and historic remakes, the Gibbs M1903A4 has a number of features that intentionally distinguish it from originals, even by the casual observer. For instance, the barrels are marked with the modern dates of manufacture, unlike original barrels that would have had 1940's manufacturing dates. Gibbs also does not remove the receiver markings, another telling feature to distinguish this historic remake. Finally, the scopes are marked with the Gibbs name and address, unlike the originals, which were marked with Weaver's manufacturer's marks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  NIB Grendel P12   .380 Semi-Auto Pistol  never fired
postcontent:
NIB Grendel P12 .380 Semi-Auto Pistol, never fired  

A great compact pistol for collecting and/or service.

Grendel was a hot manufacturer of mostly high capacity weapons in the early 90's. 
When the first assault weapon ban came, Grendel silently faded away. They were resurrected 4-5 years later as KelTec, same owner, at same Florida location. Today, KelTec is the third largest manufacturer of handguns in the USA. If this Grendel resembles a KelTec you've seen that is why. The slide, frame and firing mechanisms are made of high strength steel, with high-impact strength polymer material for the grip, mag well, trigger, trigger guard and magazines. 

This is a lot of firepower in a very small package. The .380 cartridge is no slouch and many feel that it's about top of the line for a truly concealable pistol. This P12 is much smaller and lighter than compact high capacity 9mm's and .40's handguns. Gun comes all original; in the factory plastic case, manual, parts list and 2 magazines. Manual is 14 pages, very thorough on; features, operation, disassembly, parts and cleaning. 

Magazines holds 11 rounds, with one in the chamber (P12 = 11+1). 
Design of this pistol allows it to be carried safely with a chambered round. Fire mechanism is double-action with a low inertia safety hammer system for safe carry, thus not requiring an external safety.

Technical Specs:
 Caliber .380 automatic
 Weight, Loaded 13 ounces
 Gun Length 5.3 inches
 Barrel Length 3.0 inches
 Sight Radius 4.5 inches
 Capacity 12 (11+1) rounds

title: For Sale:  Vector Arms Underfolder AK47
location: SW, by the new WalMart, Jacksonville, North Carolina
postcontent:
Up for sale is one of the better AK builds you can buy, short of a Custom Job by Krebs.  This is a Vector Arms model AUSA underfoler.  It's an Armory USA receiver put together with a matching numbers Bulgarian parts kit, the exact same build that Krebs Custom uses for their underfolders.  This isn't some pieced together crap build, AUSA receivers are 1.5 mil steel, whereas the standard AK runs a 1.0 mil receiver.   As a point of comparison, the RPK Medium Machine Gun uses a 1.6 mil receiver for rigidity.  The Bulgarian parts kits used by Vector are mint, all numbers matching.  I've fired about 400rds through this gun.  I do have the cleaning rod for it, and though it's not in the pic, it will be included.  Sights are great, shoots well with no malfunctions, and the stock is pretty tight for an underfolder.  It has paracord along the left side of the folding stock, to make it a bit more comfortable while firing.  I've shot some folders that attacked you like a rabid pitbull when firing, but this is not one of them!

I've been watching piece of crap frankengun AKs and Romanian WASR 10s imported by  Century Arms go for 1000-1200 on this website, and on others.  This blows my mind since in early December you could find them for $450 in shops, and order them for less than $400 online. Unlike the vast majority of the AKs on the market right now, this is a quality rifle, which retailed for over twice what a CAI frankengun went for before the frenzy. 

I'll sell this gun with two magazines, and all wood furniture. The Ultimak Rail, as shown in the picture, will not be sold with the gun.  I will put the stock wood back on, and it matches the wood that you see in the pics.  I will also include 100 rounds of 7.62x39 Ulyanovsk FMJ with this rifle.

I'm not desperate to sell this AK, as it's the best AK I've seen/shot/handled in a very long time.  I'll take $2000 for it.  If you're an AK fan, and you appreciate quality, then you'll know the difference between a Vector and a CAI pot luck gun.   Please don't shoot me lowball offers, if you want a cheap AK, go buy one of those frankenguns. I'm open to reasonable offers though.  If you want a quality rifle, one of the best AKs you can get your hands on, shoot me a message.

Face to face only, must show DL and sign a bill of sale, per NC General Statute.

Please no offers for car stereos, tattoo work, etc.  I might knock off some cash on a partial trade transaction for guns and gun related items.  I am particularly interested in ruger LCPs, glock 19s, and mossberg 930 shotguns.  If you have a 930 JM Pro signature series I'll knock $1000 off the price.
